Class CLUI

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.centralesupelec.is1220.CLUI.CLUI
  • public class CLUI
extends java.lang.Object

    CLUI

    This class represents the CLUI which permits the user to enter command to interact with the bike renting system.

      • setup

        public java.lang.Object[] setup​(java.lang.String[] arguments,
                                CLUI clui)
        Creates an new instance of the bike renting system when the right command is given. The default are 10 stations, 10 slots per station, an area of size 4 and 75% of slots filled with bikes.
        Parameters:
        arguments - the command of the setup function : setup -v (name of the instance) -nstations (the number of stations optional : 10 ) -nslots (the number of slots per station optional : 10) -s (the size of the square representing the area optional : 4) -nbikes (the percentage of slots occupied by bikes optional : 0.75).
        clui - the CLUI associated.
        Returns:
        the message of success or failure of the operation.
